<sentence id="1">Bacteria use two different strategies to acquire sufficient amounts of iron , namely the expression and secretion of high-affinity iron-binding compounds called siderophores , and the production of receptors for iron carriers such as heme .</sentence>
<sentence id="2">Genes involved in the biosynthesis , transport and regulation of the siderophore yersiniabactin are clustered in the high pathogenicity island of Y. enterocolitica [ 103 ] and have counterparts in P. luminescens ( plu2316-2324 ) .</sentence>
