<sentence id="11">Interestingly , three gene loci involved in iron acquisition , namely the genes encoding the hemin storage system , the yersiniabactin and the enterobactin transporter FepG , have been demonstrated to be up-regulated upon temperature decrease in Y. pestis or Y. ruckeri , respectively ( Table 1 ) .</sentence>
<sentence id="12">This large set of iron , hemin , heme and siderophore transporters underlines the importance of iron availability for the life cycles of P. luminescens and Y. enterocolitica .</sentence>
